#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.auth-server-url` is a key base OIDC URL property."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.auth-server-url` Ă© uma propriedade de URL base de chave do OIDC."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"By default, Quarkus OIDC adds a `.well-known/openid-configuration` path segment to this URL and discovers the OIDC provider metadata.\n"
"The discovery path can be customized with `quarkus.oidc.discovery-path`, for example, it can be set to `.well-known/oauth-authorization-server`."
msgstr ""
"Por padrĂŁo, o Quarkus OIDC adiciona um segmento de caminho `.well-known/openid-configuration` a esta URL e descobre os metadados do provedor OIDC.\n"
"O caminho de descoberta pode ser personalizado com `quarkus.oidc.discovery-path`, por exemplo, ele pode ser definido como `.well-known/oauth-authorization-server`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "You can disable metadata discovery with `quarkus.oidc.discovery-enabled=false` when the provider does not support it (most OAuth2 providers do not), when you would like to optimize start up time by skipping a remote discovery call and configure individual OIDC provider endpoint URLs instead."
msgstr "VocĂŞ pode desativar a descoberta de metadados com `quarkus.oidc.discovery-enabled=false` quando o provedor nĂŁo oferecer suporte a ela (a maioria dos provedores OAuth2 nĂŁo oferece), quando vocĂŞ quiser otimizar o tempo de inicializaĂ§ĂŁo ignorando uma chamada de descoberta remota e configurar as URLs de endpoint individuais do provedor OIDC em vez disso."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Individual OIDC endpoint URLs such as `quarkus.oidc.authorization-path` can also be set when you need to override one of the discovered OIDC endpoint URLs or when the discovered OIDC metadata does not include a required endpoint URL."
msgstr "URLs de endpoint OIDC individuais, como `quarkus.oidc.authorization-path`, tambĂ©m podem ser definidas quando vocĂŞ precisar substituir uma das URLs de endpoint OIDC descobertas ou quando os metadados OIDC descobertos nĂŁo incluĂ­rem uma URL de endpoint necessĂˇria."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "These URLs can be either relative to the base `quarkus.oidc.auth-server-url` URL or absolute."
msgstr "Essas URLs podem ser relativas Ă  URL base `quarkus.oidc.auth-server-url` ou absolutas."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "For example, usually you need to disable the discovery and specify individual endpoint URLs when working with OAuth2 providers, see the xref:security-oidc-code-flow-authentication.adoc#oauth2[OAuth2 providers] section for more details."
msgstr "Por exemplo, geralmente vocĂŞ precisa desativar a descoberta e especificar URLs de endpoint individuais ao trabalhar com provedores OAuth2, consulte a seĂ§ĂŁo xref:security-oidc-code-flow-authentication.adoc#oauth2[provedores OAuth2] para obter mais detalhes."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The individual OIDC endpoint URLs that you may need to configure depends on the OIDC <<application-type>> and expected token formats."
msgstr "As URLs de endpoint OIDC individuais que vocĂŞ pode precisar configurar dependem do <<application-type>> OIDC e dos formatos de token esperados."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.authorization-path`, `quarkus.oidc.token-path` and `quarkus.oidc.end-session-path` are only relevant when the <<authorization-code-flow> authentication is enabled with `quarkus.oidc.application-type=web-app`."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.authorization-path`, `quarkus.oidc.token-path` e `quarkus.oidc.end-session-path` sĂŁo relevantes apenas quando a autenticaĂ§ĂŁo <<authorization-code-flow> estĂˇ habilitada com `quarkus.oidc.application-type=web-app`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.jwks-path` is needed to fetch JSON Web Key Set (JWKS) but only if the tokens are JSON Web Tokens (JWT). When it is `quarkus.oidc.application-type=web-app`, ID tokens representing the user authentication are always in JWT format, and in most cases JWK keys are needed to verify them. The JWKS path is not needed if you work with opaque (binary) bearer access tokens which are usually remotely introspected instead."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.jwks-path` Ă© necessĂˇrio para buscar o JSON Web Key Set (JWKS), mas apenas se os tokens forem JSON Web Tokens (JWT). Quando Ă© `quarkus.oidc.application-type=web-app`, os tokens de ID que representam a autenticaĂ§ĂŁo do usuĂˇrio estĂŁo sempre no formato JWT e, na maioria dos casos, as chaves JWK sĂŁo necessĂˇrias para verificĂˇ-los. O caminho JWKS nĂŁo Ă© necessĂˇrio se vocĂŞ trabalha com tokens de acesso bearer opacos (binĂˇrios), que geralmente sĂŁo introspectados remotamente."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.introspection-path` is required in most cases when an opaque (binary) access token must be introspected remotely because such tokens can not have attached signatures that can be verified. It is worth setting `quarkus.oidc.introspection-path` even if you work with JWT tokens and your provider supports the remote token introspection. In such cases, JWT tokens can be introspected remotely as a fallback, when no matching JWK verification key has been found to verify JWT locally."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.introspection-path` Ă© necessĂˇrio na maioria dos casos quando um token de acesso opaco (binĂˇrio) deve ser introspectado remotamente porque tais tokens nĂŁo podem ter assinaturas anexadas que possam ser verificadas. Vale a pena definir `quarkus.oidc.introspection-path` mesmo se vocĂŞ trabalhar com tokens JWT e seu provedor oferecer suporte Ă  introspecĂ§ĂŁo remota de token. Nesses casos, os tokens JWT podem ser introspectados remotamente como uma alternativa, quando nenhuma chave de verificaĂ§ĂŁo JWK correspondente foi encontrada para verificar o JWT localmente."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`quarkus.oidc.user-info-path` is usually required after the <<authorization-code-flow> completion, when `UserInfo` must be requested to get more information about the user, in addition to what is already available in the ID token.\n"
"Requesting `UserInfo` is also possible for the bearer access token flow."
msgstr ""
"`quarkus.oidc.user-info-path` geralmente Ă© necessĂˇrio apĂłs a conclusĂŁo do <<authorization-code-flow>, quando `UserInfo` deve ser solicitado para obter mais informaĂ§Ăµes sobre o usuĂˇrio, alĂ©m do que jĂˇ estĂˇ disponĂ­vel no token de ID.\n"
"A solicitaĂ§ĂŁo de `UserInfo` tambĂ©m Ă© possĂ­vel para o fluxo de token de acesso bearer."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When you work with OAuth2 providers which issue binary access tokens but do not support the remote introspection, and do not have standard `UserInfo` support, `quarkus.oidc.user-info-path` must point to the OAuth2 provider specific endpoint returning information about the current user, in order to support an indirect access token verification. See the xref:security-oidc-code-flow-authentication.adoc#oauth2[OAuth2 providers] section for more details."
msgstr "Ao trabalhar com provedores OAuth2 que emitem tokens de acesso binĂˇrios, mas nĂŁo oferecem suporte Ă  introspecĂ§ĂŁo remota e nĂŁo tĂŞm suporte padrĂŁo a `UserInfo`, `quarkus.oidc.user-info-path` deve apontar para o endpoint especĂ­fico do provedor OAuth2 que retorna informaĂ§Ăµes sobre o usuĂˇrio atual, a fim de oferecer suporte a uma verificaĂ§ĂŁo indireta de token de acesso. Consulte a seĂ§ĂŁo xref:security-oidc-code-flow-authentication.adoc#oauth2[provedores OAuth2] para obter mais detalhes."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`quarkus.oidc.revoke-path` and `quarkus.oidc.registration-path` are currently not used directly by Quarkus OIDC.\n"
"Applications xref:security-openid-connect-client-reference.adoc#revoke-access-tokens[can revoke tokens] on logout, and other security events.\n"
