#, fuzzy
msgid "Rich Authorization Requests"
msgstr "Rich Authorization Requests (RAR)"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The link:https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9396[OAuth 2.0 Rich Authorization Requests] (RAR) specification enables OAuth2 client applications to specify fine-grained authorization requirements during the authorization code flow.\n"
"Instead of relying solely on traditional OAuth 2.0 scopes, RAR represents required permissions as JSON that is URL-encoded and passed as an `authorization_details` query parameter."
msgstr ""
"A especificaĂ§ĂŁo link:https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9396[OAuth 2.0 Rich Authorization Requests] (RAR) permite que aplicaĂ§Ăµes clientes OAuth2 especifiquem requisitos de autorizaĂ§ĂŁo detalhados durante o fluxo de cĂłdigo de autorizaĂ§ĂŁo.\n"
"Em vez de depender apenas dos escopos tradicionais do OAuth 2.0, o RAR representa as permissĂµes necessĂˇrias como JSON que Ă© codificado na URL e passado como um parĂ˘metro de consulta `authorization_details`."

